																		<h1 class="black"><b><a href="http://www.green-tourism.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GT-Canada.jpg"><img class=" wp-image-5554 size-full alignright" src="http://www.green-tourism.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GT-Canada.jpg" alt="" width="250" height="250" srcset="http://www.green-tourism.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GT-Canada.jpg 250w, http://www.green-tourism.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GT-Canada-150x150.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px" /></a>Welcome to Green Tourism Canada!</b></h1>
<h3></h3>
<h3><a title="Green Tourism Canada website" href="http://www.greentourismcanada.ca/" target="_blank">Visit Green Tourism Canada website</a></h3>
<p class="purple purplepara"><b>Green travel is on the rise and the tourism industry in Canada is climbing aboard. With over 2,300 members internationally, Green Tourism Canada is part of the largest and most established sustainable tourism programmes in the world. There are currently over 80 members certified or awaiting grading in BC, ranging from resorts, hotels and campgrounds to tour operators, wineries, attractions and more. </b></p>
<h2 class="purple purplepara black"><b>Green Tourism Canada Programme Background</b></h2>
<p>In 2010, the Green Tourism Programme began a pilot with 31 British Columbia tourism businesses across six tourism regions in BC. All businesses were assessed by a senior green tourism assessor from the UK and were scored against a rigorous set of sustainability indicators to determine if their performance had achieved a certification award level of Bronze, Silver of Gold.</p>
<p>In 2013, Green Tourism partnered with GreenStep Solutions Inc. to conduct the third-party assessments to tourism operators interested in becoming certified. Two senior assessors from the UK travelled to Canada to train the Canadian assessors, and now sit on the Gold Review panel for all Canadian Gold graded members. The programme remained focused on BC companies until 2015, and is now expanding into Alberta. Green Tourism Canada will be rolling out to all Canadian provinces next year, and into the USA in 2017.</p>
<h3 class="purple black"><a href="http://www.green-tourism.com/green_holidays/?Region=region_7&amp;Type=-1&amp;Grading=-1&amp;gtbs_freetext=" target="_blank">View full list of Canadian certified operators</a></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 class="black small purple"><b>Green Certification Benefits for Green Hotels &amp; Tourism Operators</b></h2>
<p class="black small purple ">As a Green Tourism Certified Member, you will receive:</p>
<ul>
<li>Third-party assessment once every two years by one of our experienced environmental advisors who will give you your grading, identify cost savings opportunities, and highlight opportunities for marketing your green message to your guests</li>
<li>Green Tourism grading seal for bronze, silver and gold members, to use in your promotional materials and website to inform guests of your commitment to sustainability</li>
<li>Grading Report with comments and advice on measures implemented and an action plan with recommendations for improvements. Summary of achievements, which can be used to help you tell your green story in your marketing. Guidance on how to gain higher grading at your next visit</li>
<li>Promotion through Green Tourism press and editorials at the regional, provincial, national and international level</li>
<li>Website listing on <a href="http://www.greentourismcanada.ca/" target="_blank">Green Tourism Canada website</a> and <a href="http://www.green-tourism.com/green_holidays/?Region=region_7&amp;Type=-1&amp;Grading=-1&amp;gtbs_freetext=" target="_blank">Green Tourism website</a> which includes a photograph, text, contact details and a link to your website</li>
<li>Regular e-update with technical information, membership updates, events, regional news and offers and discounts from green suppliers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.green-tourism.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/GTC-Brochure.pdf" target="_blank">Download a brochure</a> </strong></p>
<p class=""><b>Are you interested in learning more or becoming certified?</b></p>
<p class=""><b>Contact: Romina Rooney at <a href="tel:1-800-469-7830" target="_blank">1-800-469-7830</a> or email </b><a href="mailto:info@greentourismcanada.ca." target="_blank"><b>info@greentourismcanada.ca</b></a></p>
